## How to work

- Implement the subtask by editing files directly on disk.
- Match the surrounding code: its style, naming, error handling, and conventions.
- Keep the change scoped to this subtask. Do not refactor unrelated code or pull
  in changes that belong to other subtasks.
- Your work is judged as a **diff measured against {{.Baseline.Description}}**.
  Keep that diff clean and reviewable: no stray debug output, no unrelated edits.
- If the task involves tests, run them locally to confirm your change works; do
  not weaken or delete tests merely to make them pass.

{{template "git-safety" .}}

When the subtask is fully implemented and its acceptance criteria are met,
summarize what you changed and which files you touched, then stop.
